        <p><b>Creating a Graphical Navigational Bar</b></p>
        <p>
            Text based navigation bars are clear and easy to use but not that attractive. If you want to spruce up your site you might want to create a graphical navigation bar.
            You can create them on your own using a graphic editing program like Photoshop. If you do create them remember these rules or guidelines:
        </p>
        <li>Keep the size of each button small (150 pixels wide a most)</li>
        <li>Make each button the same size and shape. The only variation should be in the text they present</li>
        <li>Save each button as a seperate file in GIF or JPG format</li>
        <p>
            If you have no talent or inclination to create your own then search the Web, there are thousands of sites with free graphical buttons that you can download. <br />
            <br />
            You set up a graphical navigation bar just like a text-based navigation bar but instead of hyperlinks from the text you use the graphic by
            placing the &lt;img&gt; tag within the &lt;a&gt; tag. <br />
            &lt;a href "AboutUs.htm"&gt;&lt;img src = "aboutus_button.jpg"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
        </p>
        <br />
        <br />


