        <p><b>Redirecting to Another URL</b></p>
        <p>
            If you decide it is time to move and you move your Webiste to a different URL then you should leave a redirection page explaining
            what has happened to anyone who comes looking and taking them to your new website location. It is customary to include a delay of five seconds
            before the page takes to your new location. It is also required to include a text hyperlink to the new page incase the redirection doesnt work. <br />
            <br />
            You implement this redirection operation by adding an attribute to a &lt;meta /&gt; tag in the &lt;head&gt; section of the page. You must create a
            new &lt;meta /&gt; tag for this operation; you cannot add the attributes to any existing &lt;meta /&gt; tag that the document might have. <br />
            Like This: &lt;meta http-equiv = "refresh" content = "5; url = http://www/google/com"&gt;<br />
            Be sure to use a semicolon (not a comma) between the delay (the content attribute) and the url attribute.
        </p>
