        <p><b>Key Points</b></p>
        <li>A navigation bar contains a list of hyperlinks to the major pages on your site. It doesnt need to include every page on the site. The optimal number of links is between four and seven.</li>
        <li>In HTML5, you can use the &lt;nav&gt; tag as a container to indicate that a group of links constitutes a navigation element</li>
        <li>Plan your sites organization before creating your navigation bar. Draw a diagram and the pages connections to each other. Chose a file name for each page.</li>
        <li>Navigation bars are traditionally placed at the top or on the left side of the page.</li>
        <li>Many Web designers place a text version of their navigation bar at the bottom of each page four user convenience.</li>
        <li>A text-based navigation is simply a series of hyperlinks.</li>
        <li>A graphical navigation bar uses small graphics for hyperlinks. You can create these or use already created ones.</li>
        <li>To redirect a page to a different URL create a &lt;meta /&gt; tag in the &lt;head&gt; section with the http-equivalent attribute</li>

